## What I Am Still Thinking About

Something I want to understand better: how do organizations handle PCI DSS compliance when payment processing is just one small part of what they do? A hospital that accepts card payments for copays, for example, has to maintain PCI DSS compliance for that function while also managing HIPAA for everything else.

Managing two overlapping compliance frameworks simultaneously — with different audit cycles, different requirements, and different enforcement bodies — sounds genuinely complex. I imagine there is a lot of work involved in identifying where the frameworks overlap so you are not duplicating effort. That feels like a practical GRC skill I want to develop over time.

